      "content": {
        "title": "Femoral Shaft Fractures — Core Principles",
        "definition": "Diaphyseal femur fractures typically from high-energy trauma, managed with intramedullary nailing or plating.",
        "summary": "Reamed intramedullary nailing is standard for closed fractures. Floating knee and ipsilateral neck/shaft fractures require specialized fixation strategies."
      },
